export const questionObj = {"Qtext": "

Suppose triangle JKL is a right angled triangle with right angle at vertex J and JM is perpendicular to KL . If \(KL = 8 \) cm, and \(JL = 6 \) cm, then find the ratio of the areas of triangles JKL and MJL .
\newline
tikzpicture{}
\newline

", "Steps": [{"id": "s1", "n_params": 0, "step_txt": "In triangles JKL and MJL , we have
\[
	\angle KJL = \angle JML 
\]
\[
	\angle JLK = \angle JLM 
\]
So, we can write that
\[
	\Delta JKL \sim \Delta MJL 
\]
So, now we can write that
\[
	\frac{\textrm{area of } \Delta JKL }{\textrm{area of } \Delta MJL } = \frac{KL ^2 }{JL ^2 } = \frac{64 }{36 }
\]
\newline
"}]} 

 export const resp = [{"data": [], "text": " "}]
